OL,7,FJim Crombie, deputy chief executive of
OL,8,FNHS Lothian, said: "Very often when a
OL,9,Fpatient is delayed in hospital for a
OL,10,Flong time, it is because they require
OL,11,Fa significant and complex, bespoke
OL,12,Fpackage of care that is difficult for
OL,13,Fhealth and social care partnerships to
OL,14,Fprovide in the community.
OL,16,F"The issue of delayed discharge is a
OL,17,Fcomplicated challenge for the NHS,
OL,18,FHealth and Social Care Partnerships
OL,19,Fand council colleagues.
